HEADWORD: Cladophyll
<hw>Clad"o*phyll</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ a sprout
+ <?/ a leaf.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A special branch, resembling
a leaf, as in the apparent foliage of the broom (<gen>Ruscus</gen>) and
of the common cultivated smilax (<gen>Myrsiphillum</gen>).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

